<section class="page-frame py-16" aria-labelledby="how-it-works-heading">
  <div class="text-center">
    <h2 id="how-it-works-heading" class="text-3xl font-bold text-foreground">
      How it works
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-2 text-muted-foreground">
      From template source to server-rendered HTML.
    </p>
  </div>
  <ol
    class="mt-10 grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4"
    aria-label="Compilation flow"
  >
    <li class="rounded-lg border border-border bg-card p-5">
      <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-muted-foreground">1. Author</p>
      <p class="mt-1 font-medium text-foreground">
        Write a flowview region inside .astro or a standalone .flow file.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li class="rounded-lg border border-border bg-card p-5">
      <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-muted-foreground">2. Compile</p>
      <p class="mt-1 font-medium text-foreground">
        The Rust compiler parses the template and emits a plain JS render
        function.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li class="rounded-lg border border-border bg-card p-5">
      <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-muted-foreground">3. Inject</p>
      <p class="mt-1 font-medium text-foreground">
        The Astro or Vite plugin replaces the region with the generated render
        call.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li class="rounded-lg border border-border bg-card p-5">
      <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-muted-foreground">4. Render</p>
      <p class="mt-1 font-medium text-foreground">
        Astro evaluates the function at build time and emits static HTML.
      </p>
    </li>
  </ol>
</section>
